                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5801</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chinese Ministry of Foreign
                            Affairs</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Chinese Legation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="57" xml:id="d37fn57">Copy of telegram transmitted to the Department by
                        the Chinese Legation on January 9.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-09">January 9,
                            1933</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Marshal Chang Hsiao-Liang, in an interview given to Chinese and foreign
                    correspondents, declared: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Since international peace efforts appear to have ceased to be effective,
                            I see no way to maintain peace and protect China except through
                            sacrificing our lives and blood.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
            </div>
